===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally  {{och-l|*瀕}}, {{liushu|ic|nocap=1}}: a person {{och-l|*頁}} near the water's edge {{och-l|*涉}}, extended to mean "on the verge". The water component {{och-l|*氵}} was removed to distinguish its usage for "frequent".

===Etymology 1===
Perhaps from a {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*phi-r/n/s|t=late, behind, after, outside}} (STEDT root #5883). See {{och-l|比|to compare, match, follow}} for more cognates.

